Abdomen.
Terga brown with two light brown marks submedially; tracheation not pigmented. Sterna brown with one mark sublaterally. Caudal filaments lost. Genitalia (
Figure 1C
). Forceps whitish brown. Forceps segment I wide at base; 0.4 × length of segment II; distance between base of forceps (BF in 
Figure 1C
) 0.25 × distance between lateral margins of forceps (LMF in 
Figure 1C
). Forceps segment III oval, 1.5 × as long as wide; 0.1 × length of segment II. Posterior margin of styliger plate with small medial projection.

Mature nymph.
Length: body, 
6.8 mm
; cercus, 
4.9 mm
; terminal filament, 
2.4 mm
; antenna, 
6 mm
. (
n
